<p>Dep&#8217;t of State Parks did a TAKE of DPR Division for Off Highway Vehicles in the amount of $31,000,000.00 to bail out non-motorized parks State Parks Recreation Fund as they did not get enough funding. Hmmm, stealing money from OHMVRD that is a special fund that uses NO General Fund money to bail out DRP which is GF funded, and NOT a loan, but a TAKE with no repayment option. This is wrong, and in violation of Public Resources Code. Legislature approved of this THEFT.</p>
<p>Brown also allowed $10,000,000.00 PER YEAR to be taken from same Off Highway Vehicle Recreation Division user fund, and DIVERTED to pay for ON highway road work and repairs.<br />
This legislature and this governor are the KINGS of Ponzi schemes and shell games with taxpayer monies.. BS. Between the 2 TAKES we are talking $81 Million dollars from OHV Fuel Tax Revenues and trust fund monies. So much for the word TRUST in OHV Trust Fund&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.</p>
